If the DEFAULT value of a column is trivial (zero or equivalent),
- on data insertion, quickly check if a column is totally zero and don't write it on disk (see `memoryIsZero` function);
- on merging of data, do not write columns with trivial DEFAULTs that were absent in all merged parts.

create table t(a Int64, b Int64) engine = TinyLog;
create table s(a Int64, b Int64) engine = TinyLog;


select a from t left outer join s on (t.b=s.b);

CH: 0 rows in set. Elapsed: 0.001 sec.
PG: ERROR:  column reference "a" is ambiguous
mysql: ERROR 1052 (23000): Column 'a' in field list is ambiguous


select t.a from t left outer join s on (t.b=s.b) where a=1;

CH: 0 rows in set. Elapsed: 0.002 sec.
